- Oh, yes, you can. And you will.

01:36:04.530 --> 01:36:07.069
Corporal Penning has come forward.

01:36:07.070 --> 01:36:10.390
He's implicated Long and Bonner.

01:36:10.740 --> 01:36:12.870
You son of a bitch.

01:36:13.010 --> 01:36:15.909
You went to him with a fucking deal,
didn't you?

01:36:15.910 --> 01:36:19.909
- He'll do serious time.
- Yeah? How serious, huh?

01:36:19.910 --> 01:36:22.780
How serious? How much time?

01:36:23.720 --> 01:36:26.260
As much as I could get.

01:36:27.860 --> 01:36:30.189
Well, luckily for me, that means shit.

01:36:30.190 --> 01:36:32.859
You see these? Those are warrants.

01:36:32.860 --> 01:36:36.259
We have jurisdiction,
you're compelled to deliver those men.

01:36:36.260 --> 01:36:38.060
I want them now.

01:36:39.370 --> 01:36:43.269
I am not the only one who made a deal.

01:36:43.270 --> 01:36:45.839
My C.O. Talked to yours.

01:36:45.840 --> 01:36:49.820
It is just one less headache for them.

01:36:50.040 --> 01:36:52.209
It's out of our hands now.

01:36:52.210 --> 01:36:53.740
I'm sorry.

01:36:55.620 --> 01:36:57.240
I bet you are.

01:37:00.720 --> 01:37:02.819
I wanna hear the confession.

01:37:02.820 --> 01:37:05.559
Long isn't speaking.
I'll get you Penning's statement.

01:37:05.560 --> 01:37:09.399
No, I wanna hear it from his lips,
and I want him present.

01:37:09.400 --> 01:37:11.960
That's not gonna happen.

01:37:15.040 --> 01:37:17.839
How many soldiers
leave this base every night...

01:37:17.840 --> 01:37:20.239
...to go visit a bar, have a drink or two?

01:37:20.240 --> 01:37:23.809
- I know you're feeling burned.
- I'm not burned, I'm fucking pissed off.

01:37:23.810 --> 01:37:27.649
Take a guess. On an average weekend,
what, seven, eight thousand soldiers?

01:37:27.650 --> 01:37:31.119
You know what? I'm gonna sit in my car
outside any of your entrances...

01:37:31.120 --> 01:37:34.219
...and pull over every vehicle
that comes back to this base...

01:37:34.220 --> 01:37:39.329
...and I will arrest every soldier whose blood
alcohol is 1/1000 over the legal limit.

01:37:39.330 --> 01:37:42.629
- How many men would that be?
- And how long till you're fired?

01:37:42.630 --> 01:37:45.499
I'll do it on my own time,
and we have a good union...

01:37:45.500 --> 01:37:48.099
...so I'm gonna say four to five weeks.

01:37:48.100 --> 01:37:53.069
How many DUI's do you think
I could make in a month?

01:37:53.070 --> 01:37:55.130
Should we find out?

01:38:13.660 --> 01:38:15.629
<i>Commander's office.</i>

01:38:15.630 --> 01:38:21.769
<i>- Let me speak to Captain Henning, please.
- One moment, sir.</i>

01:38:21.770 --> 01:38:23.639
<i>We were leaving the strip club.</i>

01:38:23.640 --> 01:38:26.469
And we thought that Mike and Bonner
have cooled down.

01:38:26.470 --> 01:38:30.479
They could be like that,
laughing one minute and fighting the next.

01:38:30.480 --> 01:38:33.309
Anyway, we're in the car,
and Mike's all pissy...

01:38:33.310 --> 01:38:36.549
